inn1.comm: that wasn't too far from being a wide. Back of a length, well outside off stump and it them seams away prodigiously. Ah it was called a wide after all.
short of a length outside off stump, Wade stays back and defends to the off side.

dropped by Rohit Sharma at first slip. And the reason for the drop was that Rohit was positioned at second slip. This would have been a regulation take for Tendulkar to his left at first slip, but Rohit came flying across in front of him for a one-handed take. He gets his hand on it and grasses it.
on Wade's pads, and he tucks it quite crisply through the leg side for a couple.
better line, Wade handles it carefully.
draws Wade marginally forward with a fuller length, and Wade defends down the track.
full length outside off stump, driven to cover solidly
back of a length outside off, angled into Warner who is tucked up and defends from the crease.
good lengths, can't be driven and can't be pulled. The line is good too, and Warner defends.
stays on the back foot and defends again.
width now, Warner sets up nicely and flays it behind square, but Zaheer tidies up at third man.
angled across on a length, not much sideways movement for Vinay. Wade leaves.
short of a length outside off stump, Wade chops it square and picks up a single.
no confusion this time. Another big wide from Zaheer, and Davis call is there for all to see.
he gets his outside edge again. Wade just seemed to be defending inside the line there, and the ball popped softly off the outer half, on the bounce to Tendulkar at first slip.
short of a length, wide of off stump and he lets it go.
goes a touch fuller and gets the ball to straighten from wide of off stump. Impressive carry for Zaheer as Wade shoulders arms.
draws his front foot out once more, and Wade again lets the ball go through to MSD
pitched well up on the stumps, Wade defends solidly down the track.
Wade stays cautious, reaches out to a full length ball and defends into the covers. He is a slow starter, but can take off once he gets in.
short and wide, but not as short or as wide as Warner thought. He wanted to blaze it through the covers, but chops it to the off side without timing.
gets good connection on the punchy cut this time, but finds point.

electric from Kohli. This is the best Indian fielding side of all-time. Short ball outside off to Warner, who crashes it behind square and Kohli goes horizontal to his right at point to cut it off. Four runs saved.
Warner gets it away finally, stays back and steers off the face of the bat between point and cover for a couple.
Vinay plugs away short of a length outside off, and Warner covers the line to defend to the point area.
Warner squeezes another one past a prancing Kohli, and gets a single behind square on the off side.
Warner gets another single in front of point, staying back in his crease to a length ball and steering carefully.
too short to trouble Wade. He goes back in the crease and jabs a short ball towards third man for one more.
big seam movement from a shorter length. Warner stayed back and looked to lash it square, but it beat him by a good distance.
Zak goes fuller on the stumps, and Warner defends it to the off side.
gets him forward again, Warner meets it with a good forward press and plays to cover.
At long last, the first four of the day. Zaheer loses his line and strays down the leg side. Warner is inside the line and just helps it along to fine leg.
Wade looks to wallop Vinay up and over the off side, but there's just no width to work with, and he misses it completely. Strange choice of shot.
Vinay cuts one back in slightly from outside off, Wade tries to force it away square but plays it to point.
goes too straight now, Wade skips and chips it through square leg for a single.
Vinay strays down the leg side now from round the stumps, and Warner can't get the glance away. Dhoni trots across to field the leg bye.
Wade walks right across the stumps and looks to ship, and the ball is again outside leg stump. Another leg bye taken behind square.

Warner's fore-arms to the .. well.. fore. Back of a length outside off stump, angling in to cramp a normal batsman, but Warner's far from normal. He manages to power it away through the covers with a vicious jab and picks up three more.

Jadeja's turn to dazzle at point. India cut off another four. Horror ball from Zaheer, hopelessly wide of off stump and it would have been called. Warner tries to thrash it behind point, but Jadeja's dive intervenes.
width again, Warner thumps it powerfully into the covers, but straight to Raina.
Wade responds late to Warner's call for a single after he pushed it to mid-off, but no hard done. They get the single easily.
good length ball just outside off, Wade covers the line and opens the face to defend to the off side.
angled into the pads - Zaheer's having an indifferent start to his day. Wade works it through square leg for a single.

another quiet turn to the leg side gets Wade a single. Aha, Vinay hits the stumps from fine leg, and the ricochet gets Australia an overthrow. It went off the pad to begin with. Did I get anything right there?
length ball on off stump, defended to the off side.
fuller length, Wade thumps into the off side and again picks out cover.
single now, softens the grip and drops it to the off side.
Warner covers the line as he moves across and defends down the track.
fuller length, Warner just can't get them away. This time he mistimes the cover drive after plonking his front foot across.
angles into the pads, Warner nudges to mid-on for a single... Another shy, another ricochet,  but no overthrow this time.
comes in with the angle, and Warner's attempt to work it to the leg side ends up in a tangle. It hits the pad, but it was going down the leg side.

Warner will pinch himself to confirm that he has indeed got a four away through the off side. Zaheer gives him miles of width outside off and Warner does well to reach it. In fact it went off the toe end of the bat and flew between cover and point.
better line and length, Warner defends into the off side.

Zaheer's poor start continues. Over-pitched on off stump now, and Warner's shifting into gear rampantly now. Sets himself up beside the line, gets under the ball and trumpets it through the covers with a rasping drive.

shot of the afternoon! Warner's yorked the boundary skirting at long-on with a rousing pick-up punch. Friendly length ball from Zaheer, who isn't moving the ball about anymore and Warner's thumped it rather disdainfully. Jabbed through the line, and he holds the pose too with a protracted follow through.
full again, Warner looks to get forward and is a touch late on the check drive to the off side. Super over this for Aus.

Zaheer Khan goes down at third man with the grace of a Bollywood actor in an action scene, on the stunt double's off day. Width to Wade wide of off stump, and he cracks it square. Zaheer had a long way to run, and then went down like a crumbling building, but the ball slipped through.
on the pads, Wade tucks it square, and Jadeja nearly catches Warner napping with a quick pick up and throw, but he misses. Warner's in, and the 50 is up.
over-pitched just outside off stump, Warner tries to clatter it through the off side, but misses. This pitch is much flatter than the first few overs suggested.
Raina's chance now, at cover. Leaps up high to parry a hard smash into the turf that took off at pace. India are being generous with width to Warner.
short of a length outside off, Warner pushes to cover and gets a single.
that didn't swing. It landed outside leg and kept floating further down. The loosest loosener you will see, at 117 kph.
better everything. 124 kph, on off stump and keeping Warner back in the crease. He defends.
angled into the pads, he's not got the first three balls to swing. Warner stays in the crease and plays it to mid-on.
similar ball, Warner stays in the crease and plays it to the leg side with the angle.
banged away. A bit of a sissy start this for Irfan. No pace, no movement, it sits up pleasantly outside off stump and Warner shows it the way to the cover boundary.
short of a length outside off stump now, Warner cuts behind point, and Gambhir trots around from third man to stop it.
fuller length at 122 kph, Warner pushes a single to mid-on.
tossed up from round the stumps, driven off the front foot into the covers.
Warner stays back and defends behind point. Wade is again late to start for the single, but dives in to reach in time.
loopy ball on the stumps, Wade defends to the leg side.
drifted into the middle and leg line, pushed through wide mid-on for a single.
decent start from Raina. Fired in, gets the ball to straighten, and Warner works it square.
tossed up, Warner muscles it down the ground, but the Powerplay is over and long-on is back. Only a single.
Warner is looking ominous. Another length ball that does nothing off the straight, on off stump. Warner leans out and lofts it up and over mid-off quite easily. Problems for India.
full again at 132 kph, Warner creams another single to long-off, who has wisely gone back now.
Wade's turn to drive sumptuously into the covers now as Irfan over-pitches outside off stump.
short ball outside off stump, Wade cracks it behind square for a single.
full and wide, a Zaheer-type ball, and Warner somehow finds point again with his cut.

Irfan has struck. Tendulkar has taken a catch, and Rohit Sharma isn't anywhere near him this time. Soft dismissal, Irfan dangles it full with no pace on the pads, and Warner contrives to chip it uppishly straight at midwicket. India will breathe easy now. Warner looked in agony when he saw that looping straight to Sachin.
Raina moves so fast he over-runs the ball! Pitched up outside off, Wade drives it straight and Raina moves too far to his right as the ball goes to his left.
full ball to Ponting, who leans out and works it watchfully to the leg side.
shorter, Ponting goes back and nudges to the leg side.
tossed up outside off, Ponting plays it back to Raina, who is hustling him by bowling his over very quickly.
full ball outside off, defended again.
another dot, as Raina keeps it full and gets Ponting to defend to the leg side.
law of averages catches up with backward point. Jadeja misfields one. Some movement for Irfan, gets the ball to swing away, and Wade cuts hard for a single.
pitched up outside off stump, Ponting reaches out and defends to the off side.
back of a length outside off, Ponting steers gingerly to cover-point.
still on 0. Pitched up outside off, he leans out and check drives to mid-on.
pitched well up on the stumps, Ponting again drives to mid on.
Ponting is taking his time. Back of a length outside off stump, and defended to mid-off this time.
tossed up on the stumps, Wade defends to the off side.
full again, Raina's doing a top job. Defended to the off side.
Wade skips out to the flight of the ball and works it down wide of mid-on for a single.
short ball, Ponting goes back and works it to mid-on. Not looking the part. At all.
full ball, Ponting defends off the front foot again.
stop the press. Ponting has a run. Leans out and opens the face to steer a single behind point.
just when we were talking highly of India's fielding, Zaheer Khan reminds us of the good old days. Lets a Ponting off drive go straight through the legs for a single.
Wade works Irfan with the angle to square leg for a single.
pitched up on off stump, Ponting meets the ball with a forward press and plays it to mid off.
he's forward again, opens the face and guides to point.
and again, moves across and drives with a flowing blade into the covers. No intent to get a run there.
whoa, Ponting jumps out and looks to carve up and over the off side. Thick outside edge, rolls down to third man, where Vinay does well to keep the runs down to two
well left outside the off stump by Wade, just a shade outside of
tries to whack that across the line but mistimes it to long-on, hurries the single and a direct hit would have been trouble
Ponting tried to leave that but the ball hit the under edge and rolled to the keeper
Pontin tries to clip that in the air over the on side but the ball clips his pads and rolls away
Ponting tries to drive past cover but checks his shot and pats it to the off side, takes a quick single
Zaheer must have bowled three consecutive knuckle balls, Wade tries to work it to the on side but inside edges to the body
if only there had been a backward point he would have taken that comfortably, slashed on the up to the deep, Ponting looking circumspect
Wade tries to cut that but ends up chopping it down to cover
clips it to the leg side and Wade slips at the crease when turning around for the second, there was no second run anyway
gets across and pushes it softly down the track
good running, he punches it in front of mid-on and sets off quickly for the single
fractionally short  and a touch too wide and Wade fails to capitalise, he can only chop it down to point
Zaheer hides the seam again, he gets behind the line and pushes it down the track

Ponting's struggle ends! He falls for the trap thanks to some intelligent field placing, drifts on the pads and he tries to loft over the leg side but ends up finding Irfan at deep backward square leg
excellent running, he drops it with very soft hands in front of the stumps and sets off quickly
slower ball outside the off stump, Forrest is happy to let it go
gets across and pushes it with soft hands towards cover
he loses control of that slower ball and slips it very wide outside off
gets across and defends inside out to the off side, wasn't in control of that shot
135.1 kph, good delivery from Vinay angling in sharply from round the wicket, he gets it to move away after pitching and beats Wade
slower ball and Wade shapes to slash it away but is foxed by the change of pace, could have got a nick there, it bounced before reaching Dhoni
another excellent delivery! A jaffa which has Wade all at sea, the batsman withdraws the shot and drops his glove just as the ball fizzes past his blade
slashes and makes proper contact this time, places it down to square third man
inside edge onto the thigh and the ball rolls to the off side
goes back at the crease and chops it to the off side
goes back at the crease and chops it to the deep on the off side
goes back and punches it to short cover
this one drifts and beats the outside edge! Close call
goes back, waits for the turn and punches it to sweeper cover
full on the stumps and pushed down the ground to long-off
a bit too short and he goes back and punches it to long-off
142.5 kph, not the best of starts, short and wide and Forrest carves it over cover point, looked a touch risky at first
139.3 kph, keeps it a touch closer to the off stump line and he's happy to leave it alone
146 kph, much better, pitched up a bit further and invites the slash, beaten for pace
139.8 kph, bangs it in short and he has Forrest ducking
145.5 kph, keeps it a touch outside the off stump and Forrest shoulders arms
148 kph, straight on the body and he has to hurry on the back foot to defend
punches it to the off side and he sets off but quickly rushes back to his crease
gets forward and drives down to mid-off
goes back and punches it down towards long-off
goes back at the crease and chops him down to point
Wade uses his feet and tries to force it past the off side but can't beat cover
gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
tries to paddle it around the corner but fails to make proper contact
146 kph, clips it down to mid-on
fuller delivery and he pushes it down to mid-on
ouch! Tendulkar's shin gets a hammering, outside edge which drops well short of Tendulkar at first slip, he gets his shin in the way, he seems to be fine now, no worries
short and slashed away down to third man, good running by Wade as he makes it well in time, before Gambhir's throw arrives
makes a bit of room and crashes it down to mid-off and well stopped
bangs it in short on the body and he uneasily clips it in the air down to short square leg
clips it to the on side
goes back and punches it to the off side
that's huge! As Shastri would have said. Comes down the track and lofts him high over wide long-on, Wade breaks the shackles
he leaves it to the keeper
gets forward and punches it to the off side
fullish on the pads and he clips it to mid-on
152 kph, cranks up the pace further, he shuffles and clips him to the leg side
146 kph, bangs it in short and too quick for Wade as he arches back and tries to upper cut it over the slips
gets across and works him down  towards deep backward square leg
defends inside out towards point and he tells his partner to stay back
a touch too full and in the right slot for Wade to play the booming off drive past mid-off and cover, Yadav needs to keep it a bit short to him
Rohit comes round the wicket, gets well forward and drives down the track
full again and clipped to the on side
over the wicket to Wade, he gets across and pushes it to the off side
the bowling change works for India, Rohit cut back on the pace a bit, drew Wade forward for the chipped drive but he ended up spooning it straight back at Rohit, easy catch
goes back at the crease and he punches it to long-off
too wide down the leg side and he fails to make contact
drifts on the body and he clips it back to the bowler
on the blockhole and he squeezes it back to the bowler
defends to the off side

Comedy of errors! The third umpire presses the wrong button would you believe it! Appeals for a stumping and Dhoni is quite confident, Raina bowls from round the wicket and beats Hussey on the drive through the off side, Hussey drags his back foot back and a part of his boot is behind the crease so he's safe, he was always not out but incredibly the screen said "out" and Hussey quiety made his way back, Billy Bowden ran after him and called him back. "It's not April 1 yet, mate", he must have said. Hussey gets a surprise gift, Dhoni however didn't see the funny side to it and had a word with the umpires
pushes it wide of point for a couple
goes back at the crease and punches it to long-on
short and pulled! Hussey rocks back at the crease and clubs it over midwicket
gets forward and pushes it down to sweeper cover
comes round the wicket, he pushes it down to cover
gets across and stabs it to the off side
drifts on the pads and he clips it to midwicket
punches it back to the bowler
opens the face and steers it to point
stays back and punches it down to long-on
tucks him up for room and he punches it down the track
drives down to mid-on
gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball rolls to short third man
comes down the track and he gets an outside edge to the off side
clips him down to square leg for a single
drops it with soft hands towards Raina and risks a single to Raina, Dhoni failed to collect the throw and Forrest was in trouble, Dhoni was not behind the stumps
goes back and clips him down to midwicket
goes back and punches it past cover
Chance, Over Rohit Sharma at short midwicket, short and pulled and Rohit tries to cup it over his head, needed lightning quick reflexes
clips it behind square leg
goes back and defends back to the bowler
makes room and punches it down to cover
lobbed in the air, Hussey tries to paddle it away and gets a top edge that drops at the vacant square leg region
rocks back and plays a short-arm pull down to long-on for a couple
drifts on the pads and he clips him wide of long-on
angles across him and he opens the face and dabs it down to third man
148.3 kph, nice and straight and Forrest is hurried on the back foot to defend
fullish on the off stump and he pushes it down the pitch
126 kph, gets a hint of away swing and he dabs it down to point, good stop
he gets a bit of width and he opens the face and steers him down to third man
tucks him up for room and he has to arch back to defend
pulled and he wasn't in control of that, luckily it was wide of mid-on
Hussey beaten outside off, good delivery by Irfan tucking him up for room
a touch too short and he chips down the track and angles it down to third man
Forrest stays rooted to the crease and tries to cut but misses, Irfan has created two chances this over
drifts on the pads and he clips him down to midwicket
full and swinging away and Hussey squirts it to mid-on
on the blockhole and Forrest plays all over that one, manages to dig it out and the ball rolls to the off side and they steal a run
goes on the back foot and defends it down the track
goes back at the crease and angles it down to third man
outside off and he lofts it down to sweeper cover but it drops well short of Jadeja, risky shot
short of a length outside off and Hussey goes for the slash and misses it, close call again
131.8 kph, angles on the body and the ball clips his pads and rolls away
slapped that! Drops it short of a length from round the wicket, sits up nicely for Hussey to bludgeon that in front of square on the on side
making good use of the vacant spaces here Hussey, short and wide outside off this time and Hussey rolls his wrists and cuts wide of backward point
back of a length and he punches it down to point
opens the face of the bat and he angles it wide of third man for a couple
goes back at the crease and punches it down the track
goes back and defends

Dropped Hussey chips down the pitch and tries to smash that over mid-off, Yadav had it covered, tried to cup it over his head and the ball slipped out, there was an outside chance of him taking it on the rebound if his reflexes were a bit better, that's the 50 stand
shuffles and works it to the on side
drives down the track and just beats the diving Zaheer
on the blockhole and he drills it out
slower bouncer and Forrest didn't know what to do with it
he's gifted a half volley on the pads and he moves across and clips it down to fine leg, used the  pace of the ball there
fast full toss and Hussey fails to put that away, punches it back to the bowler
141 kph, too short by Yadav, sits up nicely for Hussey as he swivels and plays the short-arm pull over square leg
too straight and he clips it wide of fine leg
punches it to the off side for an easy single
Forrest plays an odd-looking shot, looked like he slapped that down to mid-off who was a bit deep
bangs it in short down the leg side and he swivels to pull but misses, wide called
full on the pads and he clips it down to square leg
another full toss and Hussey stabs it past the bowler, long-off mops up
goes back at the crease and knocks it back it to the bowler
squirts out a yorker outside the off stump and Kohli fields at point
had to scramble there, Hussey mistimed the pull down to mid-on and decided to risk a single to Jadeja, dives but a direct hit would have sent him back
full on leg and he punches it down to long-on
if Irfan drops it short at that pace, he's asking for trouble, Forrest fetches that from the off stump and clubs it over midwicket
a bit too wide this time and he reaches out and pushes it past point
slices it down to sweeper cover and Forrest contemplates a double but wisely sent back
clips it across the line down to midwicket
drops it short and he has time to go back and pull it in front of square
fetches a short delivery from outside the off stump and pulls but can't beat mid-on, that's his fifty
full on the pads and squeezed down to long-off
goes back at the crease and angles it down to point
no slip and Forrest intelligently dabs it down to third man, the ball was a touch flat and skidded through but Forrest kept his eyes on the ball
full on the pads and drilled down to long-on
goes back at the crease and punches it behind square on the off side
another boundary behind the wicket, this time he drifts on the pads and Hussey gets a gentle tickle to get it past the diving short fine leg fielder
comes down the pitch and he clips him wide of deep midwicket
short and wide and he reaches out and places it wide of cover
beaten for pace as the ball clips his pads and rolls away
slower ball and he clips it away off his pads down to square leg
short and he pulls it, not in full control but safe, down to long leg, that's another impressive fifty by Forrest
drops it to the off side for a quick single and Hussey dives at the crease, Yadav fails to pick up and throw

some relief for India here! Credit to Irfan for his clever change of pace, Hussey gives the charge but wasn't ready for the slower ball outside off, tries to swing it across the line and doesn't get the elevation or the distance, down Raina's throat at deep midwicket
too wide outside the off stump for him to play a shot
nips it back in from the off stump and he clips it with the angle to midwicket
deftly dabbed down to third man and Yadav does well to pick up and fire the throw to Dhoni but the keeper, not for the first time, failed to get behind the stumps, Forrest really had to dive
a bouncer and Irfan is penalised
pounds a low full toss to long-off

double-strike for Irfan! Forrest whips a length delivery on the pads in the air down to deep midwicket, the ball dips on Kohli but he does well to dive and take the catch on the tumble, his 'love affair; with the crowd continues as he makes another gesture to the crowd behind him., this time it didn't seem like anything offensive
bouncer to start the over
clipped to the on side and they have to hurry the single
148 kph, makes room to a full delivery and carves it down to deep point for a couple
makes room and angles it down to third man
too straight on the pads and he clips him to fine leg
drills a fast yorker down to long-off
makes room and pushes it down to point
clips his pads and it rolls to the on side, Irfan appeals
Irfan's banging in the bouncers, this was too high despite Hussey ducking
tucks him up for room and he can only block it back to the bowler
Hussey squirts it just past the diving Irfan Pathan to his right
shuffles and clips him down to fine leg
a touch wide and he reaches out  and slaps it to the deep on the off side
exquisite lofted drive! Perfect length for Hussey to make a bit of room and crisply loft him over the sight screen, follow through was perfect
makes room and carves it to sweeper cover
slower delivery and he pulls it down to deep midwicket
fires it on the blockhole and he makes room and squirts it to the off side
makes room and forces it to sweeper cover, Yadav does well to limit that to a single
makes room and squirts out a full ball straight to point
drifts on the pads and he clips it to the leg side
hoicks a length delivery down to deep midwicket, didn't control if but good enough to take two
full delivery swinging in and he drills it down to long-off
Irfan totally lost control of that slower ball there! Tried to release it using his wrists like Murali, too wide outside the off stump
on the blockhole and it goes between his legs and a diving Dhoni gets a glove to it, the ball rolls to fine leg
goes right across his stumps and tries to paddle it down to fine leg, drops it short of short fine leg
he foxes Christian with a slower ball and he's still penalised for height, seemed a bit harsh at first considering the batsman was down the track
smashes that one down the ground, Christian comes down the track and hammers a length ball over the bowler's head
and again! Fuller delivery on the pads and he whams that so hard down the ground that long-on had no chance, brute power

the helicopter shot! Comes down the track and hammers a full delivery outside off down to long-off, the follow through was something else, Dhoni would have been proud of that, but he's not smiling now
now he goes across his stumps and paddles it down to fine leg! He beats short fine leg and it;s four consecutive boundaries
full on the pads and he clips it down to deep midwicket
some relief for Vinay as he bowls the slower ball and beats him outside off
Beware of Christian! Fractionally short of a length on the off stump and he clubs that behind square on the on side, the bat speed was something else
good comeback, the yorker and he plays all around it, can't steal a leg bye
near-perfect yorker again, goes between his legs and he nearly loses balance at the crease
the slower ball and Christian picks it early and hoicks it over midwicket, the fielder in the deep may have been a bit too forward
full on the pads and he clips it in the air down to deep square leg
goes past Dhoni! Yorker on the pads, he makes room and the ball clips his pads, sneaks past the stumps and Dhoni moved to the wrong side, it evaded him and raced to third man

inn2.comm: that knocks four off the target straightaway, swinging in and landing on the half volley, crisply driven down the ground wide of long-of
swings away and he squeezes it out back to the bowler
down the leg side and Gambhir tries to run it down to fine leg and the bowler thought he got a touch to it
inside edge on the drive and Forrest dives at square leg but can't cut it off cleanly
swings it away outside the off stump and he leaves it alone
swings it towards the off stump and he clips it towards mid-on, didn't look very comfortable when running
he gets a fizzer from Lee straightaway, balloons up and Tendulkar fends it off one hand close to his face, luckily it drops short of Lee
fends off another short one to the off side and takes the single easily this time

Lee has got rid of the in-form man! Peach of a delivery on the corridor outside the off stump, Gambhir was tentative on the defense, didn't move his feet across and he was beaten for a bit of extra pace too, thin edge taken by Wade
stays right behind the line and defends
wide and quick and he chops it towards slip, gets an under edge
gets behind the line and punches it to the off side
steers it with the angle down to cover and pushes Kohli for the single, Tendulkar's shin seems to be fine, no apparent discomfort there
short of a length and he goes back and defends
a touch too wide and he opens the face of the bat and dabs it down to third man
induces the false shot! Pitches it up and swings it away and Tendulkar slashes and misses
he oversteps! Too full outside off and he can only drive it back to the bowler
Free Hit And Tendulkar fails to put it away, to the bowler's credit, it was quite difficult to hit, on the blockhole outside off
another slash outside the off stump, Tendulkar's rooted to the crease
141 kph, angles it on the body and he stays back and defends
143.8 kph, Lee keeping it tight here, Kohli goes back and defends it solidly
fuller in length and Kohli gets forward and solidly defends that
crashed off the front foot and extra cover fumbled, the ball really flew off the bat on that occasion
he tries to create a scoring opportunity by giving room but he steers it down to point

There's an appeal for a catch to mid-on and the umpire Davis perhaps reckoned that hit his helmet, in fact he was right, it was a brute of a delivery that kicked up and balooned off the helmet and mid-on (Doherty) ran forward and took it, Davis was not interested, all the Australians thought they had him
short outside off and he carves it over cover point
